# Pythia demo config profile.
#
# Copy this to `demo.env` (the default, git-ignored) and edit, or keep several
# named profiles and select one per run:
#
#   cp demo.env.example demo.env            # becomes the default profile
#   ENV_FILE=demo.consumer.env ./demo up    # pick a specific profile
#
# `./demo` sources the selected file and exports every assignment, so the values
# reach both the bash stack scripts (up.sh) and the Python client (ask/repl/MCP).
# Anything left commented out falls back to the built-in defaults.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MODE 1 — all-local demo (DEFAULT)
# Leave everything below commented out and `./demo up` launches ONE local EDC
# provider connector per logical provider in scripts/demo/lib/datasets.py
# (currently 3: rheinmobil, zugspitze, donautech), plus a consumer connector and
# the mock data server, and seeds each provider with only its own datasets.
# Ports are assigned by scripts/demo/lib/topology.py:
#   rheinmobil → mgmt :19193 / dsp :19194
#   zugspitze  → mgmt :39193 / dsp :39194
#   donautech  → mgmt :49193 / dsp :49194
#   consumer   → mgmt :29193 / dsp :29194
# `./demo ask` fans out across all three and returns the best-matching dataset.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MODE 2 — local consumer, remote providers
# Uncomment this block to run ONLY the consumer connector locally and talk to
# providers that run on separate servers (no local provider, mock, or seeding).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# CONSUMER_ONLY=1

# The consumer connector to drive. Default is the local connector; only change
# this if your consumer runs elsewhere.
# PYTHIA_MANAGEMENT_URL=http://localhost:29193/management
# CONSUMER_MGMT=http://localhost:29193/management

# The remote providers, as a JSON array of {dsp, id}. `id` must match each
# provider connector's EDC participant id. Replace the hostnames with the real
# servers (one provider per server).
# Single-quote the whole value so the shell does not strip the inner double
# quotes when this file is sourced (JSON needs them).
# PYTHIA_PROVIDERS='[{"dsp":"https://provider1.example/protocol/2025-1","id":"rheinmobil"},{"dsp":"https://provider2.example/protocol/2025-1","id":"zugspitze"},{"dsp":"https://provider3.example/protocol/2025-1","id":"donautech"}]'

# Management API auth (must match the consumer connector's config).
# PYTHIA_API_KEY=password
# PYTHIA_API_KEY_HEADER=X-Api-Key

# TLS for the direct client→provider data-plane fetch. One shared bundle/cert is
# used for all providers, so PYTHIA_CA_BUNDLE must contain every provider CA.
# PYTHIA_VERIFY_SSL=true
# PYTHIA_CA_BUNDLE=/path/to/all-provider-cas.pem
# PYTHIA_CLIENT_CERT=/path/to/client-cert.pem
# PYTHIA_CLIENT_KEY=/path/to/client-key.pem
